



✅ STAR Script 3 — Challenging Project (XR Silicon Bring-Up Under Extreme Deadline)
Situation

I led the camera bring-up for a new XR silicon platform that introduced a dual-mode camera feature. Early builds were highly unstable with crashes, freezes, deadlocks, and black-screen issues.

Task

Deliver a stable bring-up within a 2–3 day deadline, while ensuring deep root-cause fixes rather than temporary patches.

Action

Systematically reproduced and intentionally triggered failures to capture stack traces and RAM signatures

Performed deep-dive debugging across software, driver, and system layers instead of only triaging logs

Collaborated closely with cross-functional teams and guided root-cause analysis

Onboarded two junior engineers to parallelize execution while I retained technical and decision leadership

Documented issues, fixes, and learnings to enable faster future bring-ups

Result

Successfully completed bring-up within the deadline

Resolved multiple stability and reliability issues permanently

Created reusable debugging documentation to accelerate future bring-ups

Appreciated by stakeholders for technical leadership under pressure